      "content": "i get the \"official\" line, but that's exactly what i'm talking about. if you look at the way certain flight telemetry data from the apollo era was \"lost\" or simply not preserved, it's super suspicious. it's not even about whether they went, it's about why they went to such extreme lengths to make it look like a simple scientific mission. why would a government agency be so protective of the specific geological or structural details found in those early surface samples if there was nothing to hide? it feels like a massive gap in the narrative.",
